8 Standing Committee on Revenue shall conduct a study on the
9 advisability and feasibility of treating as a single entity for the
10 purposes of the commerce tax imposed by chapter 363C of NRS:
11 (a) A business entity primarily engaged in the business of
12 renting real property located in this State to other persons, which has
13 more than 50 percent of the value of the ownership interest of the
14 business entity owned or controlled, directly or constructively
15 through related interests, by common owners.
16 (b) A limited liability company, and any series thereof,
17 primarily engaged in the business of renting real property located in
18 this State to other persons.
19 (c) Any other type or form of entity engaged primarily in the
20 business of renting real property located in this State to other
21 persons which the Committee determines is advisable to study.
22 2. On or before January 1, 2027, the Joint Interim Standing
23 Committee on Revenue shall submit a report of the results of the
24 study, including, without limitation, any recommendations for
25 legislation, to the Director of the Legislative Counsel Bureau for
26 transmittal to the 84th Session of the Nevada Legislature.
